✅ 1. Build the Project
Click on the Build icon (or press F7) to compile the code and check for errors.

✅ 2. Start the Debugger
Click Debug > Start/Stop Debug Session from the menu bar, or press Ctrl + F5.

✅ 3. Use Step Controls
Once in the debugger mode, use these toolbar buttons or shortcuts:

Action	Toolbar Icon	Shortcut
Step Into	
F11
Step Over	
F10
Step Out	
Shift + F11
Run (Continue)	▶️ (Play icon)	F5
Stop Debugging	■ (Stop icon)	Ctrl + F5

✅ 4. Watch Variables & Memory
Use the "Watch" window, "Locals", or "Memory" view to observe variable changes.

Go to View > Watch Windows > Watch 1 to track variable values live.

✅ 5. Set Breakpoints (Optional)
Click on the left margin next to a line of code or press F9 to set a breakpoint.
